  <p>
    In a new-construction project full of choices, the septic system is unusual: it's one of the few
    elements that can tell you where you can and can't build, rather than simply fitting in wherever
    it's told. That's why it belongs near the front of the planning process. Left until late, it can
    force expensive rework; planned early, it quietly shapes a site plan that works.
  </p>

